                        Contents of Mushroom disk 33
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

ý
    This disk contains 4 rather handy utilities for you to use.

û
                               SAnalysisV2.2
                               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~

ý
    This is a small program, which tells you the current settings of your
system. It is handy to put in the startup-sequence of a disk, as it looks
for things like external drives, and tells you exactly how much CHIP and
FAST memory you have. The program was written by Asa Margetts.

û
                              Disc Cat V2.11
                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

ý
    This extremely handy little program catalogues the contents of all of
your floppy drives. It comes as 2 programs, the first will hold up to 5,000
entries, and the second will hold up to 10,000 entries. Both programs will
work on a 1Mb machine, but it reccomended by the author that you use the
ÿ
ý
5,000 version until your list gets a bit full.

    You can then save this list to a disk file, or search through it for
any particular program name. Written by Gary Hoyles, this is one
reccomended disk utility.

û
                               MenuPRO V1.2
                               ~~~~~~~~~~~~

ý
    Written again by Asa Margetts, this little program allows you to
control WB operations from within AMOS. It stores paths etc. for operations
such as PPMore files, and you can then access them directly from the click
of a mouse.

    The program was designed as a front-screen for compilation disks. It
will hold up to 10 entries, and all instructions for using the program are
situated in the DOC file which accompanies the program.



